# Build context exclusions for the chat-server Dockerfile.
#
# Inputs the Dockerfile actually needs from the repo root:
#   - go.mod, go.sum
#   - pnpm-lock.yaml, pnpm-workspace.yaml, package.json, tsconfig.json
#   - apps/, packages/
#   - migrations/
#   - top-level internal/  (introduced by #789 — must NOT be excluded)
#
# scripts/ is intentionally NOT in the input set: scripts/build-single-binary.sh
# is the host build path, not used inside the Docker build.

# Node / JS build outputs
node_modules
**/node_modules
dist
**/dist
.pnpm-store

# Go build outputs
bin
*.exe
*.test
*.out

# Local dev SQLite databases
.dev.db
.dev.db-*

# VCS / CI / agent state
.git
.gitignore
.github
.claude
.claude/worktrees

# Tests / e2e artefacts (Playwright report + raw test trees not needed in image)
tests
playwright-report
test-results
.last-run.json

# Editor / OS noise
.DS_Store
.idea
.vscode

# Linkedin / planning artefacts (out of image scope)
linkedin-posts
specs
diary
CHANGELOG.d

# Documentation / repo metadata not needed at build time
README.md
CHANGELOG.md
CLAUDE.md

# NOTE: do not exclude `internal/` — sub-issue #789 introduces a top-level
# internal/buildinfo/ package the go-build stage must see.
